description: India is set to finalize a significant Rs 63,887 crore deal with France on Monday for 26 Rafale-Marine fighter jets, primarily for the INS Vikrant. The agreement, encompassing 22 single-seat and four twin-seat Rafale-M jets, includes weapons, training, and maintenance support.
title: 64k crore deal for 26 Rafale-M jets to be inked with France on Monday

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack on tourists, J&K Lt Governor Manoj Sinha has directed Army Chief General Upendra Dwivedi to hunt down all perpetrators and supporters involved.
title: Attackers must pay heavy price: J&K LG Manoj Sinha to Army chief

description: A Delhi court has deferred issuing notices to Sonia and Rahul Gandhi in the National Herald money-laundering case. The Enforcement Directorate (ED) sought the court's directive to hear the accused before cognizance of the chargesheet, citing new legal provisions. However, the court has directed the ED to rectify missing documents in the chargesheet before proceeding further.
title: Bring missing files, court tells ED, halts notices to Gandhis

description: The Centre defended the Waqf (Amendment) Act, 2025 in the Supreme Court, asserting its secular nature and dismissing claims of religious interference. The government highlighted that mandatory registration of waqf properties, a key point of contention, has existed for a century.
title: Centre tells SC waqf law 'secular', says petitioners 'spinning a false narrative'

description: Jammu and Kashmir administration demolished the houses of three terrorists involved in the Pahalgam attack. The houses belonged to Adil Hussain Thoker, Asif Sheikh, and Ahsan Sheikh. Authorities ensured no family members were inside during the demolitions. This action aims to deter local terrorism and support for terror. The administration warns of further consequences for those who join terror ranks.
title: J&K: Houses of 3 Pahalgam terrorists demolished

description: Sudeep Neupane, a 27-year-old Nepali citizen, was tragically killed in the Pahalgam terror attack. Mistaken for an Indian Hindu, he was shot before he could clarify his nationality. His body was repatriated to his hometown in Butwal, Nepal, after a journey across India.
title: J&K terror attack: Medic was shot before he could ID self as Nepalese

description: Dr. Krishnaswamy Kasturirangan, the former ISRO chairman and architect of the National Education Policy 2020, passed away at 84 in Bengaluru. He spearheaded significant ISRO missions, including the Chandrayaan planning, and later revolutionized India's education system.
title: Pole star for India's space journey & edu reforms

description: The Supreme Court has cautioned Rahul Gandhi regarding his remarks against V.D. Savarkar, hinting at potential suo motu action if he continues to denigrate the freedom fighter. While staying a lower court summons against Gandhi, the bench, led by Justice Dipankar Datta, reminded him of Indira Gandhi's past praise for Savarkar.
title: SC raps Rahul on Savarkar remarks: 'Not the way you treat freedom fighters'

description: A tragic incident occurred in Bahraich, Uttar Pradesh. A rice mill's dryer exploded, resulting in five fatalities. Three workers sustained serious injuries. The explosion happened around 7 am in Gulam Alipura area. Local residents assisted in evacuating the injured. The deceased include individuals from UP and Bihar. Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath expressed grief over the unfortunate event.
title: UP: 5 die in Bahraich rice mill blast

description: Tamil Nadu Governor R.N. Ravi alleged that state VCs were warned against attending a Raj Bhavan conference, a claim the DMK government refuted, calling the conference 'illegal'. Ravi accused the government of threatening VCs, while the Higher Education Minister criticized Ravi for defying the law after a Supreme Court verdict favoring the state in VC appointments.
title: VC meet sparks faceoff between Tamil Nadu governor & govt

description: Jharkhand minister Sudivya Kumar Sonu faced criticism for demanding Himachal Pradesh CM's resignation following the Pahalgam terror attack. Sonu claimed his remark was sarcastic, intended to highlight the Centre's silence on security issues. BJP leaders condemned his statement as irresponsible, with Babulal Marandi accusing him of bringing shame to the state.
title: Wrong facts or 'pure sarcasm'? Jharkhand mantri stirs a row

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah has directed state Chief Ministers to enforce the immediate revocation of various visa categories for Pakistani citizens, excluding long-term, diplomatic, and official visas. CMs are tasked with identifying and ensuring the departure of affected individuals by specific deadlines in late April. Stricter actions are to be taken against those who overstay, including detention and deportation.
title: Amit Shah dials CMs, says ensure Pak nationals quit India by deadline

description: The Delhi High Court has directed A.R. Rahman and Madras Talkies to deposit ₹2 crore after finding their song 'Veera Raja Veera' from 'Ponniyin Selvan 2' to be a copyright infringement of the 'Shiva Stuti' composed by the Junior Dagar brothers. Justice Prathiba M.
title: AR Rahman song identical to Dagar bros' work: Delhi HC

description: Congress attributed the Pahalgam attack to security and intelligence failures, highlighting the targeting of Hindus as a Pakistan-orchestrated attempt to incite unrest. The party criticized the BJP for allegedly exploiting the tragedy to create division and demanded accountability from the Modi government, emphasizing the need for effective counter-measures beyond symbolic gestures.
title: Congress targets govt: Security, intel failure behind Kashmir attack

description: India is set to implement its decision regarding the Indus Waters Treaty. Amit Shah chaired a meeting to finalize the implementation roadmap. The plan includes desilting rivers and dams as an immediate step. India aims to create additional water storage and speed up hydro-power projects. The goal is to maximize the use of western rivers' water within India.
title: Govt explores ways to stop water flow to Pakistan

description: India has suspended visa services for Pakistani nationals, effective immediately, and revoked most existing visas following the Pahalgam attack. Exceptions include diplomatic, official, and long-term visas. Pakistani citizens holding other visa types must leave India by specific deadlines in late April, or face legal action under the new Immigration & Foreigners Act, 2025.
title: Govt revokes 14 categories of visas for Pakistani nationals

description: A SIT report alleges ex-CM Y S Jagan Mohan Reddy was the "final recipient" of kickbacks from distilleries in Andhra Pradesh, starting in 2019. The alleged scam involved coercing distilleries to pay commissions, with funds laundered through hawala networks. The money trail purportedly leads to senior YSRCP figures before reaching Jagan, with suspect Booneti Chanakya playing a central role.
title: Jagan 'final recipient' of Andhra booze scam kickbacks, says SIT

description: Following the Pahalgam massacre, the ceasefire along the Line of Control is showing signs of strain, with small arms fire reported across multiple locations since Thursday night. The Indian Army has responded effectively to Pakistani firing, with heightened alert levels and increased fighter sorties by the IAF. Military options for punitive strikes against Pakistan are under consideration.
title: J&K: Small arms fray LoC ceasefire, big guns silent for now

description: India is intensifying diplomatic pressure on Pakistan following the Pahalgam attack, seeking international support to address cross-border terrorism. Numerous nations, including the US, Denmark, and the Netherlands, have expressed solidarity with India. External affairs minister Jaishankar briefed his Saudi Arabian counterpart on the attack's links to Pakistan, a crucial diplomatic move.
title: New Delhi briefs more envoys as it steps up outreach

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, a grim discovery was made: the trousers of approximately 20 male victims were unzipped or pulled down. Officials believe this indicates terrorists attempted to ascertain the victims' faith before their execution.
title: Pahalgam massacre: 'Trousers of 20 men were pulled down to find out faith'

description: Security forces have intensified search operations across six districts of the Jammu division to locate terrorists believed to be hiding in forest areas. This follows a gunfight in Udhampur where a Special Forces soldier was killed. Combing operations are underway in Kishtwar, Rajouri, Kathua, and Poonch, with heightened efforts to sanitize the Kathua-Samba region after recent encounters.
title: Search ops in 6 Jammu districts intensified to track down hiding terrorists

description: Jammu and Kashmir police have detained a pony service provider, Aiyaz Ahmad Jungal, following a viral video where a tourist alleged he questioned her about her religion. The tourist claimed this occurred during a mule ride in Pahalgam, two days before the terror attack.
title: Pahalgam attack: Police detain pony rider after he asked a tourist her religion

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack and advice from the Omar Abdullah-led government, Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha has convened a special J&K assembly session on April 28. Army Chief General Upendra Dwivedi met with Sinha, urging decisive action to bring the attackers to justice. The National Conference had formally requested the special session after the recent attack.
title: Special J&K assembly session on Monday over Pahalgam attack

description: Pakistan's defence minister, Khawaja Asif, admitted on Sky News that Pakistan has harbored and funded terror organizations, claiming they were doing the West's "dirty work" for decades. He stated these groups are essentially one religiously organized entity with different fronts. Asif also accused India of staging the Pahalgam attack and threatened retaliation for any Indian aggression, urging US intervention.
title: Pak defence minister admits his country harbours terror organisations

description: Kashmir's chief cleric Mirwaiz Umar Farooq, after a month of restrictions, delivered a Friday sermon at Srinagar's Jamia Masjid, condemning the Pahalgam massacre and honoring the victims. He recalled his father's assassination and expressed solidarity with the bereaved families. Mirwaiz lauded Kashmiris' hospitality, highlighting locals' efforts to help victims, including the sacrifice of Adil Hussain.
title: At first Friday prayer in weeks, Mirwaiz slams Pahalgam carnage

description: Nineteen states are challenging the Trump administration's policy on diversity in schools. They filed a lawsuit against the Education Department's directive. The directive threatened to cut funding for non-compliance. States argue the directive harms students and schools. They say it puts federal funding at risk. Earlier, judges blocked parts of the directive in three states.
title: 19 states sue Trump administration over DEI programs in public schools

description: Following the Pahalgam attack that killed 26 Hindus, the US has strongly supported India in hunting down the Islamist terrorists responsible. US officials, including Intelligence czar Tulsi Gabbard and President Trump, have pledged full support to India, signaling a departure from previous administrations' cautious approach.
title: Pahalgam terror attack: 'Hunt them down', says US amid support for action by India

description: The Balochistan Liberation Army (BLA) claimed responsibility for a roadside bomb attack in Quetta, resulting in the deaths of ten Pakistani military personnel and injuries to three others. The attack, which targeted a bomb disposal squad vehicle in the Margat area, involved a remote-controlled improvised explosive device.
title: 10 Pakistani soldiers killed in Quetta bombing, BLA takes responsibility

description: The Trump administration has seemingly reversed its controversial SEVIS termination policy, reactivating records for numerous international students across the U.S., even those not involved in lawsuits. This shift follows widespread criticism and legal challenges to the abrupt terminations, which were often based on questionable NCIC data.
title: SEVIS being restored in US; relief for impacted Indian students

description: The Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) has achieved a significant milestone by conducting a scramjet combustor ground test for over 1,000 seconds at its Hyderabad facility. This successful test validates the design for long-duration scramjet combustors, paving the way for full-scale flight testing. This advancement is crucial for India's Hypersonic Cruise Missile Development Programme, enabling high-speed, long-duration flight capabilities.
title: DRDO takes major step towards next-gen hypersonic cruise missiles

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad broke their losing streak with a dominant five-wicket victory over Chennai Super Kings at Chepauk, marking their first win at the venue. SRH's pace attack, led by Harshal Patel's 4 for 28, restricted CSK to 154. Ishan Kishan's 44 and a late partnership sealed the win, boosting SRH's playoff hopes while deepening CSK's struggles.
title: IPL 2025 Points Table: Latest standings after CSK vs SRH match

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad spoiled MS Dhoni's 400th T20 appearance, defeating Chennai Super Kings by five runs. Harshal Patel's impressive 4 for 28 led SRH's dominant pace attack, restricting CSK to 154 in pursuit of 149. Despite resistance from Brevis and Mhatre, CSK lost wickets consistently, ultimately succumbing to SRH's relentless bowling performance.
title: IPL: Harshal's four-fer shines as CSK crumble in Dhoni's 400 T20 match

description: Usha Vance, an Indian-American, is gaining prominence alongside her husband, US Vice President JD Vance. While Usha navigates political life, her sister, Shreya Chilukuri, excels in engineering. A Duke University graduate, Shreya contributed to missile development at Raytheon and now works at ASML, a leading semiconductor company.
title: Usha Vance isn’t the only high achiever in her family— Meet her sister, Shreya Chilukuri

description: Aleksander Barkov exited Game 2 against the Tampa Bay Lightning after a collision with Brandon Hagel, casting a shadow over Florida's 2-0 victory and their 2-0 series lead. Hagel received a five-minute major for interference, a decision disputed by the Lightning's coach. The Panthers now face uncertainty regarding Barkov's availability for Game 3.
title: Aleksander Barkov injury: Florida Panthers' captain departs Game 2

description: Veteran spinner Amit Mishra has strongly criticised Riyan Parag's captaincy and performance after Rajasthan Royals' defeat to Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Mishra highlighted Parag's errors during crucial moments, including a dropped catch and poor shot selection, contributing to the loss. RR's batting faltered despite promising starts from Jaiswal and Jurel, while Hazlewood's exceptional bowling sealed RCB's victory, ending RR's playoff hopes.
title: Amit Mishra lambasts Riyan Parag: 'Why blame others?'
List of countries from where it's 'nearly impossible' to get a US visa

description: The World Food Programme reports its Gaza food stocks are depleted due to Israel's blockade, impacting hundreds of thousands relying on charity kitchens. These kitchens, supporting 80% of Gaza's population with 644,000 daily meals, face imminent closure. Israel's actions, including cutting off supplies, aim to pressure Hamas for hostage release.
title: No fruits, vegetables, milk or meat left in Gaza as WFP runs out of food stocks

description: A senior Russian general, Yaroslav Moskalik, was killed in a car bombing in Balashikha, a Moscow suburb. The incident occurred on the same day a US envoy met with Vladimir Putin, raising suspicions of Ukrainian involvement. Russian authorities have launched a criminal investigation, with a foreign ministry spokeswoman accusing Kyiv of escalating attacks and attempting to disrupt ceasefire talks.
title: Senior Russian military personnel killed in targeted car bombing

description: Sourav Ganguly has firmly advocated for severing relations with Pakistan following the deadly terrorist attack in Pahalgam, which resulted in 26 fatalities. He emphasised that terrorism should not be tolerated and strict measures are essential. The BCCI has condemned the attack, observing a minute's silence and wearing black armbands during an IPL match as a mark of respect.
title: Sourav Ganguly backs severing ties with Pakistan after Pahalgam attack

description: Jharkhand's minister Sudivya Kumar stirred controversy by demanding Himachal CM's resignation following the Pahalgam terror attack. Later when he tried to clarify his remarks, he ended up taking the name of PDP chief Mahbooba Mufti instead of Omar Abdullah who is the chief minister of J&K.
title: 'Sukhu should resign for Pahalgam': J'khand min's gaffe, botched coverup

description: In an exclusive interview, President Trump stated his belief that Canada becoming the 51st US state is the only viable solution, claiming the US loses billions annually supporting them. Liberal leader Mark Carney confirmed that in his last call with Trump in March, Trump raised the issue but was respectful about Canada's sovereignty.
title: 'Canada is an interesting case': Trump says he's not trolling with talks of 51st state

description: In a thrilling IPL 2025 match, Kamindu Mendis of Sunrisers Hyderabad stunned spectators with an extraordinary catch, dismissing Dewald Brevis. Mendis's athletic feat is already being touted as the 'Catch of the Tournament'. Earlier, Ravindra Jadeja and Noor Ahmad faced unexpected umpire inspections, leading to bat replacements due to regulation failures.
title: Catch of IPL 2025? Mendis pulls off stunner to dismiss Brevis - Watch

description: Israel marked Holocaust Remembrance Day amidst the Gaza conflict, with a ceremony at Yad Vashem. Prime Minister Netanyahu likened Hamas to Nazis, a comparison Yad Vashem discourages. A Holocaust survivor, Gad Fartouk, broke protocol, calling for the return of hostages held in Gaza.
title: Israel's Netanyahu calls Hamas 'Nazis' at Holocaust memorial

description: Shreyas Iyer's impressive IPL 2025 performance, marked by significant scores and consistency against spin, has sparked discussions about his potential return to the national team. Sunil Joshi, Punjab Kings' spin coach, attributes Iyer's success to his hunger for challenges and leadership qualities. Iyer's technical adjustments and team-oriented approach further contribute to his resurgence.
title: Punjab Kings coach reveals reason behind Shreyas Iyer's resurgence

description: Following the deadly terrorist attack in Pahalgam, which claimed 26 lives, US Director of National Intelligence Tulsi Gabbard voiced strong support for India. Gabbard condemned the attack, affirmed solidarity with India and Prime Minister Modi, and expressed condolences to the victims' families. US officials, including President Trump, have reiterated their commitment to supporting India in combating terrorism.
title: US offers full support to help India hunt down terrorists

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad's dominant bowling performance against Chennai Super Kings was overshadowed by co-owner Kavya Maran's expressive reaction to a dropped catch. Harshal Patel's dropped catch of Ravindra Jadeja sparked Maran's visible frustration, quickly going viral. Despite the let-off, Patel rebounded with a four-wicket haul, showcasing the emotional highs and lows of the game.
title: Watch: Kavya Maran's animated reaction to Harshal Patel's drop catch

description: In the hours after the Pahalgam massacre, where 26 people were executed by Pakistan-backed terrorists, the world followed its usual script—India condemned, Pakistan denied, and the West euphemised. But this time, something changed. The sharpest response didn’t come from New Delhi or Washington—it came from ordinary Pakistanis, who didn’t defend the state but ridiculed it. On social media, they didn’t rage against India. They mocked their own power cuts, fuel shortages, and economic collapse. In a country where laughter is all that’s left, post-tragedy grief turned into post-collapse satire. The lights may flicker, but the punchlines never miss.
title: Why Pakistanis are trolling themselves over 'war' with India

description: Apple is accelerating its iPhone production shift to India, aiming to manufacture all US-bound iPhones there by 2026 due to US tariffs on Chinese imports. This ambitious plan requires doubling India's current iPhone output.
title: How China is trying to stop Apple’s ‘big’ iPhone move to India
24 hours to file petition: What happens when US asks an 'illegal immigrant' to leave?

description: In an unusual incident during the IPL match between Chennai Super Kings and Sunrisers Hyderabad, Ravindra Jadeja's bat failed the umpire's inspection due to size regulations. This forced Jadeja to change his bat immediately after Sam Curran's dismissal. Sunrisers Hyderabad chose to bowl first after winning the toss, leading to strategic lineup changes for both teams.
title: Drama at Chepauk! Jadeja's bat fails umpire's gauge test - Watch

description: In Balaghat district, Madhya Pradesh, four tribal girls, including three minors, were kidnapped by seven individuals on April 23 after a wedding reception. The girls were intercepted while returning to their village. All the accused have been identified and are now in police custody, facing charges under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, POCSO Act, and SC/ST Act.
title: Four tribal girls gangraped by 7 in MP

description: Melinda Gates addressed criticisms from tech leaders like Elon Musk and MacKenzie Scott regarding her philanthropic endeavors, emphasizing her commitment to impactful work through the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation and Pivotal Ventures.
title: ‘I’m doing the work’: Melinda Gates responds to Elon Musk, Bezos' ex-wife criticism

description: Following a meeting with Home Minister Amit Shah, Union Jal Shakti Minister CR Paatil announced a detailed plan to prevent Indian river water from flowing into Pakistan. The government is considering short, medium, and long-term strategies, including immediate desilting of rivers.
title: 'Not a drop ...': Roadmap ready to leave Pakistan high & dry

description: IndiGo is suspending Delhi-Tashkent and Delhi-Almaty flights until at least May 7, 2025, due to the continued closure of Pakistan's airspace for Indian carriers, forcing longer routes. Air India flights to the West may require refueling stops depending on wind conditions and aircraft load. The closure impacts approximately 50 IndiGo international routes, potentially increasing airfares by 30-40%.
title: Pakistan airspace closure: IndiGo to suspend Tashkent & Almaty flights

description: Sethuraman Panchanathan, the Indian-origin Director of the National Science Foundation, resigned amid alleged pressure from the Trump administration to cut the NSF's budget and staff. Frustration over potential budget cuts and conflicts with DEI priorities seemingly led to his departure. Panchanathan emphasized the importance of maintaining US scientific dominance and collaboration with Indian institutions.
title: Top US scientist of Indian-origin quits after DOGE hatchet slashes science

description: Mohammed Shami etched his name in IPL record books by becoming the first bowler to claim a first-ball wicket for the fourth time, dismissing Shaik Rasheed in the SRH vs CSK match. Rasheed and Ayush Mhatre also made history as the second-youngest opening pair in IPL history, with a combined age of 38 years and 131 days.
title: Unique record! Mohd Shami makes IPL history as first bowler to ...

description: Donald Trump stated Crimea would remain with Russia. He suggested Volodymyr Zelenskyy should make concessions. Trump accused Zelenskyy of prolonging the war. He also criticized Vladimir Putin for strikes on Kyiv. Recent Russian attacks on Ukrainian cities have intensified. Western leaders accuse Putin of stalling negotiations. Zelenskyy mentioned Ukraine accepted a ceasefire proposal earlier.
title: 'Crimea will stay with Russia,' says Trump in new pressure tactic on Ukraine

description: MS Dhoni expressed concerns about the MA Chidambaram Stadium pitch, preferring the old red soil surface from before 2010. Pat Cummins chose to bowl first due to the dry surface and potential dew, a decision Dhoni also favoured. CSK made changes, bringing in Dewald Brevis and Deepak Hooda, as both teams aimed to improve their standing after recent setbacks.
title: Dhoni not sure about Chepauk pitch, says 'the old red soil wicket was good'
How are America's elite universities financed?

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, India has taken decisive actions, including suspending the Indus Waters Treaty and downgrading diplomatic ties with Pakistan. Visas for Pakistani nationals are suspended, and the Attari border crossing is closed. The Indian Navy conducted missile tests, and the Air Force launched a major drill.
title: India's 10 bold moves within 72 hours of Pahalgam terror attack

description: Following a terrorist attack in Pahalgam, India has suspended the Indus Waters Treaty with Pakistan, halting data sharing and potentially allowing for increased water usage from the western rivers. This action marks a significant escalation in tensions, threatening Pakistan's water supply and agriculture, though immediate impact is unlikely due to infrastructure limitations.
title: Indus water pact suspended: How India can punish Pak

description: MS Dhoni marked his 400th T20 match, joining an elite group of Indian cricketers. His career, highlighted by a T20 World Cup win and five IPL titles with CSK, showcases his enduring impact. Despite CSK's current struggles, Dhoni's tactical acumen and unwavering fan support continue to define his legendary presence.
title: New record! 43-yo MS Dhoni becomes 4th Indian to...

description: Siddharth Sagar, known for his comedy, discussed his time on The Kapil Sharma Show, clarifying he never felt threatened by Kapil Sharma or Krushna Abhishek. He shot for the show for eight months before it moved to Netflix, and wasn't upset about not being asked to continue. Siddharth now prioritizes his peace of mind above all else in his career.
title: Siddharth Sagar reacts to Kapil Sharma not inviting him for his show

description: Shah Rukh Khan's absence from Mannat impacts local vendors, while Shatrughan Sinha questions religious emphasis after a terrorist attack. A dancer from Riteish Deshmukh's film tragically died, and Rakesh Roshan's financial sacrifices for Hrithik's debut are revealed. Amidst controversy following the Pahalgam attack, Fawad Khan and Vaani Kapoor's film faces removal from YouTube India, sparking widespread reactions and condolences.
title: SRK's move from Mannat leaves vendors worried, Shatrughan reacts to attack: Top 5 news

description: President Trump claimed that Chinese President Xi Jinping called him amidst a tense tariff battle where neither country seems willing to concede. ​"Will you call President Xi if he doesn’t call you?" Trump was asked. 'No,' he replied. 'Has he called you yet?' he was asked. The answer was positive. 'When did he call you?' Trump was asked. "He's called. And I don't think that's a sign of weakness on his behalf," Trump said.
title: Trump says Xi called him after China claimed no tariff talks going on

description: Saikat Chakrabarti, ex-aide to Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, will contest against Nancy Pelosi in 2026. He aims for California's 11th Congressional District. Chakrabarti said he respects Pelosi's service but seeks change. He believes the Democratic Party needs fresh ideas. Chakrabarti co-founded Justice Democrats. He aided Ocasio-Cortez's 2018 win. He faced criticism for social media posts. He also drew flak for a T-shirt choice.
title: Who is Saikat Chakrabarti? Indian-origin man challenging Nancy Pelosi

description: Annabel Elliot, Queen Camilla's sister, admits she still finds it hard to curtsy to her, even after 20 years of Camilla's royal life. Despite relaxed royal customs, curtsying remains common, especially for insiders like Elliot. While she may skip the formality, Elliot's support for Camilla is steadfast, serving as her emotional anchor through recent challenges.
title: Why Annabel Elliot, Queen Camilla’s sister, refuses to curtsy her

description: When 26 people were methodically executed in Kashmir’s Pahalgam valley — identified by name, religion, and in some cases, their inability to recite Islamic prayers — the global media did what it does best: looked away, chose its words carefully, and reached for the comforting vocabulary of denial. Not terrorism. Not jihad. Just “gunmen,” “militants,” and the ever-useful “tensions.” Because in the moral economy of modern newsrooms, the value of a life — and the weight of a headline — depends on who the victims are, and who the killers pray to.
title: Why Western media loves to call terrorists 'gunmen'

description: SmackDown after WrestleMania 41 will feature Undisputed Champion John Cena and Cody Rhodes. The Street Profits, Motor City Machine Guns, and DIY will battle in a TLC match for the WWE Tag Team Titles. A mysterious wrestler reveal is also scheduled, possibly Aleister Black. The event emanates live from Fort Worth, Texas, setting the stage for Backlash.
title: WWE SmackDown preview, streaming details: Full match card, highlights

description: Intel mandates employees to work from the office four days a week starting September 1, 2025, as announced by CEO Lip-Bu Tan during the Q1 2025 earnings call. This shift from the previous hybrid model aims to foster collaboration, faster decision-making, and stronger team connections.
title: Intel mandates 4-day office work from Sept 1; CEO says ‘wanted to tell you early’

description: Serbian students, already known for cycling to France, have begun a 2,000-kilometer run to Brussels to highlight corruption and demand the rule of law in Serbia. Starting from Novi Sad, over 20 students are participating in this relay-style marathon, aiming to draw the EU's attention to their struggle against President Aleksandar Vucic's government.
title: After cycling to France, Serbia's students run to Brussels to stir EU attention

description: Raja Iqbal Singh of the BJP has been elected as the new Mayor of Delhi, securing 133 out of 142 votes after the AAP withdrew from the race, alleging BJP-engineered defections. The BJP's strength in the MCD has increased since 2022, further bolstered by the inclusion of BJP MLAs as members. AAP leaders have accused the BJP of manipulating the MCD election process since 2022.
title: BJP leader Raja Iqbal Singh is new Delhi mayor

description: RPG Enterprises Chairman Harsh Goenka recently shared his insights on navigating the stock market's volatility, drawing a humorous comparison to Bollywood stars. He advised retail investors to view market downturns as opportunities to buy quality stocks at discounted prices.
title: Harsh Goenka to retail investors: “Yaad rakho: Investing ka asli hero woh hai jo…

description: Mumbai Indians are making a strong comeback in IPL 2025, securing four consecutive wins and climbing into the top four, fueled by Rohit Sharma's resurgence. After a slow start, Rohit has found his form, notching back-to-back half-centuries, which is his first time since 2016. His performance is boosting the team's chances as they aim to solidify their playoff spot.
title: 'He changes the game': Pollock calls Rohit’s revival the 'coolest' resurgence

description: Indian cricket legend Virender Sehwag advises young IPL sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi, cautioning him against complacency. Despite Suryavanshi's impressive debut and lucrative contract, Sehwag stresses the importance of long-term dedication, citing Virat Kohli's enduring career as an example. Sehwag warns that early success doesn't guarantee lasting impact, emphasizing the need for sustained performance and grounded perspective.
title: Sehwag warns 14-yo Suryavanshi: 'Seen many players who get fame ...'

description: Following the deadly terrorist attack in Pahalgam, Rahul Gandhi met with Jammu and Kashmir CM Omar Abdullah and visited victims in Srinagar, emphasizing the need for national unity against divisive forces. He assured full support from the Congress party to both state and central governments. Gandhi also attended an all-party meeting, condemning the attack and backing government measures against terrorism.
title: 'Stand united & defeat terrorism': Rahul visits Pahalgam, meets victims

description: California's GDP surpassed Japan's in 2024, reaching $4.1 trillion, driven by its thriving tech industry and property market. Governor Newsom cautioned that President Trump's tariff policies threaten this economic growth, leading to a lawsuit challenging the tariffs' legality. California, along with other states, argues these tariffs harm businesses and residents, while the White House dismisses the challenge.
title: California’s GDP hits $4.1 trillion in 2024; surpasses that of Japan

description: Virat Kohli's stellar form continues as he scored his fifth half-century in IPL 2025, leading Royal Challengers Bengaluru to a crucial 11-run victory against Rajasthan Royals. Kohli's impressive 70 off 42 balls propelled RCB to 205/5, which their bowlers defended successfully. Dinesh Karthik praised Kohli's hunger and adaptability, highlighting his reflection on past performances.
title: 'I'm too small a person to even speak about it': DK in awe of 'champ' Kohli

description: The Centre defended the Waqf Amendment Act in the Supreme Court, asserting its alignment with established practices and valid legislative power. The government refuted claims of violating fundamental religious freedoms, emphasizing inclusiveness with non-Muslim representation in Waqf bodies.
title: 'Valid, lawful exercise': What Centre told SC on Waqf row in 10 points

description: A Delhi court has deferred issuing notices to Sonia and Rahul Gandhi in the National Herald case, directing the Enforcement Directorate to rectify defects and provide more relevant documents. This development follows the ED's April 9 chargesheet, which alleges money laundering involving Rs 5,000 crore. The matter has been scheduled for hearing on May 2.
title: Court refuses to issue notice to Sonia, Rahul in National Herald case

description: Neeraj Chopra and his family have faced social media abuse after he invited Pakistani athlete Arshad Nadeem to the Neeraj Chopra Classic. Chopra expressed his deep hurt at having his integrity questioned and emphasised his commitment to India. He clarified that the invitation was a gesture of sportsmanship, and Nadeem's participation is now unlikely due to prior commitments.
title: 'Hate and abuse uncalled for': Neeraj Chopra's uncle on social media vitriol

description: India is considering allowing foreign firms to hold up to 49% ownership in its nuclear power plants, aiming to boost its nuclear sector and reduce carbon emissions. This move, under evaluation since 2023, seeks to replace coal-based power with greener alternatives.
title: India may allow 49% foreign investment in its nuclear power plants

description: The Reserve Bank of India significantly increased its gold reserves by 57.5 tonnes in FY25 amidst global financial instability and rising gold prices. This acquisition, the second largest since 2017, aligns with a global trend of central banks bolstering gold holdings.
title: RBI’s gold buying spree continues with 2nd highest purchase in 7 years

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, India responded firmly, prompting Pakistan to issue threats against any "misadventure." India summoned Pakistan's diplomat, declared military diplomats persona non grata, and suspended the Indus Water Treaty and SAARC Visa Exemption Scheme. Pakistan's airspace was closed for Indian airlines.
title: 'We will make them pay if ... ': Pakistan issues threat to India amid Pahalgam attack

description: Meta is implementing layoffs in its Reality Labs division, impacting Oculus Studios and the VR fitness app Supernatural, acquired in 2023. This restructuring aims to improve efficiency and concentrate on future mixed reality experiences, although it will result in fewer new workout releases for Supernatural users.
title: Meta lays off more employees in another round of job cuts

description: Air India is in talks with Boeing to acquire approximately 10 Boeing 737 MAX aircraft, initially intended for Chinese clients who declined delivery due to trade tensions with the U.S. This potential acquisition would bolster Air India Express's fleet and support the airline's expansion plans.
title: China’s snub to India’s advantage? Air India may buy 10 Boeing planes rejected by China

description: Pakistan's defence minister admitted to undertaking "dirty work" for the United States and the West for three decades, acknowledging it as a mistake that led to suffering. Following the Pahalgam attack, which resulted in 26 deaths, the government responded by suspending the Indus Waters Treaty, closing the Attari ICP, and reducing diplomatic staff.
title: 'Doing dirty work for US': Pak defence minister on support for terror groups

description: Gold futures saw a slight increase on Friday, starting at Rs 96,120/10 grams, while silver remained relatively flat. Mixed settlements were observed in both domestic and international markets yesterday. Gold prices rebounded above $3,300 per troy ounce due to increased U.S. unemployment claims and China's potential economic stimulus.
title: Gold rate today: MCX gold futures open higher at Rs 96,120 per 10 grams

description: Kapil Sibal proposed a special Parliament session to address the Pahalgam terror attack, emphasizing national unity against terrorism. He advocated for an unanimous resolution and international diplomatic efforts, including sending delegations to major countries to build pressure on Pakistan. Sibal also suggested leveraging India's market to influence nations trading with Pakistan and pushing for a UN Security Council resolution.
title: Kapil Sibal suggests PM form special session to discuss Pahalgam attack

description: The Supreme Court has put a hold on the Allahabad High Court's decision to not dismiss summons against Rahul Gandhi in a defamation case related to his comments on Veer Savarkar. The apex court cautioned Gandhi about making disrespectful statements about freedom fighters, particularly Savarkar, who is highly respected in Maharashtra. The court, notably, referenced historical context, pointing out that Rahul Gandhi's grandmother, former Prime Minister Indira Gandhi, had written a letter praising Savarkar.
title: 'Not how you treat freedom fighters': SC pulls up Rahul over remarks on Savarkar

description: Security forces eliminated a Lashkar-e-Taliba associate, Altaf Lalli, during an operation in Bandipora district, Jammu and Kashmir. Two police personnel sustained injuries in the exchange of fire and were hospitalized. The operation was initiated following intelligence about terrorist presence in the Kolnar Ajas area. This action follows a recent attack in Pahalgam where 26 people were killed.
title: Top terrorist Altaf Lalli killed in encounter in J&K's Bandipora

description: Following the terror attack in Pahalgam, scared tourists found refuge in the homes of Kashmiris, who opened their doors and hearts. These acts of kindness transcended fear, with families like the Maliks offering shelter and refusing payment, prioritizing the safety of tourists over business.
title: Pahalgam attack: Kashmiri families open hearts & homes to tourists

description: The Bombay High Court has admitted Kunal Kamra's petition seeking to quash the FIR filed against him by an MLA over his comedy show. The court directed Mumbai police not to arrest Kamra during the petition's pendency but allowed the investigation to continue.
title: Bombay HC grants protection from arrest to Kunal Kamra in ‘traitor’ jibe case

description: Government officials admitted a security lapse regarding the Pahalgam terror attack. They stated that such an attack was not expected. An all-party meeting was held where opposition parties supported the government's actions against terrorism. Defence Minister Rajnath Singh highlighted the government's zero-tolerance policy. Home Minister Amit Shah and S Jaishankar briefed President Droupadi Murmu on the situation.
title: Failed to anticipate Pahalgam terror attack: MHA, IB at all-party meet

description: Gold futures saw a slight increase on Friday, starting at Rs 96,120/10 grams, while silver remained relatively flat. Mixed settlements were observed in both domestic and international markets yesterday. Gold prices rebounded above $3,300 per troy ounce due to increased U.S. unemployment claims and China's potential economic stimulus.
title: Gold rate today: MCX gold futures open higher at Rs 96,120 per 10 grams

description: Google is mandating a return to the office for some remote employees, requiring them to work in a hybrid model three days a week or risk job loss. This shift affects Google Technical Services and Human Resources, with relocation assistance offered to those within 50 miles of an office.
title: Google to remote staff: Return to office 3 days a week or leave

description: In the wake of the Pahalgam terror attack, two men named Adil Hussain are at the center of the story. Adil Hussain Thokar, a wanted LeT operative, is accused of orchestrating the assault after receiving training in Pakistan. Conversely, Syed Adil Hussain Shah, a pony handler, is being hailed as a hero for his bravery in attempting to stop the terrorists and protect tourists during the attack.
title: In Pahalgam attack, one Adil drew blood, another shed it saving others

description: Chennai Super Kings will clash with Sunrisers Hyderabad in a vital IPL 2025 match. Both teams need a win to boost their playoff hopes. CSK aim to regain dominance at Chepauk while SRH seek batting consistency. The weather is expected to be hot at Chepauk with spinners slated to come into play. The head-to-head record between these two teams favours CSK.
title: IPL match today: CSK vs SRH - all you need to know

description: Delhi Police apprehended social activist Medha Patkar on Friday due to a defamation case filed by Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena in 2001. This action followed a Delhi court's issuance of a non-bailable warrant after observing Patkar's deliberate defiance of its sentencing order, specifically regarding probation bonds and a fine of Rs 1 lakh.
title: Medha Patkar arrested in defamation case after Delhi court issues non-bailable warrant

description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's high-profile romance has sparked speculation among fans, with some believing it's a prelude to Swift's next heartbreak album. The couple's very public displays of affection and constant media attention mirror Swift's past patterns of turning personal pain into chart-topping music.
title: Fans speculate Taylor's romance with Travis is building up to a breakup album

description: Apple plans to shift iPhone assembly for the U.S. market to India by next year, driven by tariff threats and geopolitical risks. This move aims to produce over 60 million iPhones annually in India by 2026, doubling current output. The shift reflects a broader strategy to diversify away from China, with India's government providing incentives to boost electronics manufacturing.
title: Apple’s China exodus: All US iPhones to be made in India by 2025

description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov stated Russia's readiness to negotiate with the US on Ukraine, emphasizing that certain elements require further refinement. He defended recent attacks on Ukraine, asserting that they targeted military objectives or civilian sites used by the military.
title: Kremlin 'ready to reach a deal' with US on Ukraine: Russia's Lavrov

description: Asian stocks surged, mirroring Wall Street's rally, fueled by Alphabet's strong earnings and renewed trade optimism under President Trump. Despite Nissan's profit warning, its shares rose on turnaround hopes. Positive sentiment was bolstered by potential US-South Korea trade understanding and anticipation of earlier Federal Reserve interest rate cuts, even amidst US-China trade talk uncertainties.
title: Asian stocks rise on Wall Street rally and trade optimism

description: Javelin star Neeraj Chopra addressed criticism for inviting Pakistani athlete Arshad Nadeem to the Neeraj Chopra Classic in Bengaluru, scheduled for May 2025. He clarified the invitation preceded the Pahalgam attacks and condemned the ensuing hate directed at him and his family. The two-time Olympic medallist emphasised his patriotism and the event's aim to promote Indian sports, stating Nadeem's participation is now impossible.
title: 'Hurt and angry': Neeraj breaks silence on inviting Nadeem for NC Classic

description: Virat Kohli's record-breaking 26th T20 half-century at Bengaluru's M. Chinnaswamy Stadium propelled Royal Challengers Bengaluru to their first home win of the IPL 2025 season against the Rajasthan Royals. Kohli surpassed Alex Hales for most fifties at a single venue and also overtook Chris Gayle in fifty-plus scores in T20 cricket.
title: IPL 2025: Virat Kohli breaks tie with Chris Gayle on T20 record

description: Authorities in Jammu and Kashmir demolished the house of Adil Thokar, a local terrorist implicated in the Pahalgam attack that resulted in 26 fatalities. Thokar, who received terror training in Pakistan, allegedly aided Pakistani terrorists in the recent assault.
title: J&K: Houses of two local terrorists involved in Pahalgam terror attack demolished
Pahalgam terror attack: Memories are all that they have now

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, BSE Sensex and Nifty50, opened in green on Friday. While BSE Sensex crossed the 80,100 mark, Nifty50 went above 24,350.
title: Stock market today: Sensex up over 300 points; Nifty50 above 24,300

description: The Indian embassy in Washington defended freezing the Indus Water Treaty with Pakistan, citing Pakistan's support for terrorism and civilian casualties. India asserts that cooperation is impossible while Pakistan sponsors cross-border terrorism, leading to the treaty being held in abeyance.
title: 'Can't expect to cooperate': Indian embassy in US on govt freezing Indus Water Treaty

description: Harvard University is reportedly negotiating the sale of approximately $1 billion in private equity fund interests, facilitated by Jefferies Financial Group, to Lexington Partners. This divestment aims to enhance liquidity amidst market instability and challenges in divesting companies. The move follows Harvard's recent announcement to secure $750 million in Wall Street financing as a precautionary measure.
title: Harvard in talks to sell $ 1billion in private equity holdings: Report

description: Stock market recommendations: Bajaj Broking Research suggests a positive outlook for the Indian stock market, highlighting Lemon Tree Hotels and Electrosteel Castings as top picks. Nifty is expected to reach 24,550 and potentially 24,850, while Bank Nifty aims for 56,800.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for April 25

description: North Korean cyber spies have been running two U.S.-based companies, Blocknovas LLC and Softglide LLC, in violation of Treasury sanctions. These entities, registered with fabricated information, were used to distribute malware targeting individuals in the cryptocurrency industry. The FBI seized Blocknovas' website, confirming a law enforcement action against North Korean cyber actors using fake job postings.
title: Revealed: Two US Cos created by North Korean spies, What Google maps showed

description: Pakistan vehemently denied involvement in the Pahalgam attack, attributing it to alleged Indian oppression in J&K and persecution of Muslims. Citing the abrogation of Article 370 and the waqf bill, Pakistan claimed India's actions fueled violence and marginalized minorities.
title: 370, waqf: Pak lists triggers for 'cycle of violence'

description: A collective of voluntary organizations reports significant strides in combating child marriage in India. In 2024-25, over 1,351 child marriages were halted and over 1.2 lakh were prevented through legal and community interventions across 416 districts. West Bengal, Tamil Nadu, and Bihar recorded the highest number of FIRs in cases where marriages could not be stopped.
title: In '24-'25, 1,351 child marriages stopped in 416 districts: Report

description: The Election Commission and the Centre informed the Supreme Court that the NOTA option has been largely ineffective, with winning candidates consistently securing significantly more votes. The court is considering whether a minimum vote percentage should be required for winning candidates, even in uncontested elections, a scenario that has become increasingly rare.
title: NOTA 'failed idea', never got a fraction of total votes, says EC

description: Pakistan has reacted strongly to India, threatening retaliation if water flow under the Indus Waters Treaty is disrupted, viewing it as an act of war. They've suspended agreements, severed ties, and warned of a forceful response, raising concerns about escalating tensions between the two nuclear-armed nations. India has not officially responded to Pakistan's threat.
title: Pak says diverting Indus water 'act of war', suspends Simla pact

description: Puneet Jaggi, a promoter of Gensol Engineering, has been detained by the Enforcement Directorate. He will be questioned about alleged FEMA violations. The probe focuses on potential fund diversions for foreign exchange acquisition. Searches occurred in Delhi, Gurgaon, and Ahmedabad. Anmol Jaggi, his brother, is expected to be summoned soon.
title: ED detains BluSmart's Puneet Jaggi

description: 'Kesari 2' has now completed 7 days at the box office but the film has not yet crossed the Rs 50 crore mark. It has seen a dip in the numbers during the weekdays but Emraan Hashmi's 'Ground Zero' which releases today may further give it competition.
title: 'Kesari 2' box office day 7: Akshay Kumar starrer inches towards Rs 50cr

description: A massive anti-Naxal operation is underway in the Chhattisgarh-Telangana-Maharashtra tri-junction, targeting the CPI (Maoist) core area. Nearly 5,000 security personnel have reportedly surrounded 300 Naxalites, including top commanders like Hidma.
title: Massive anti-Naxal op targets 'core' stronghold

description: Shubham Dwivedi, a Kanpur businessman, was killed by terrorists in Pahalgam, Kashmir, shortly after his wedding. His wife, Aishanya, recounted the horrific incident where a terrorist questioned their religion before shooting Shubham. During CM Yogi Adityanath's visit, Aishanya demanded retribution.
title: Pahalgam attack: UP bizman's wife treasures the shirt he last wore

description: Gurgaon residents Rachna and Himanshi share a tragic connection, both losing their young husbands to terrorism shortly after their weddings. Rachna's husband, Rupin Katyal, died in the 1999 IC-814 hijacking, while Himanshi's husband, Lt Vinay Narwal, was killed in the recent Pahalgam terror attack.
title: IC-814, now Pahalgam attack: Honeymoon couples caught in terror crosshairs — 26 yrs apart

description: Following the tragic terror attack in Kashmir's Pahalgam, Himachal Pradesh is bracing for a potential surge in tourism. With many travelers cancelling Kashmir trips, Himachal, like Uttarakhand, is expected to see increased footfall. While tourism stakeholders express sorrow for Kashmir, they acknowledge the likely shift.
title: Many tourists cancel Kashmir bookings, footfall may rise in Himachal Pradesh

description: A family from Kozhikode, Kerala, experienced a horrific incident during a zip-lining adventure in Baisaran. Nihal, while filming his cousin, inadvertently captured footage of terrorists opening fire on innocent people. Gunshots disrupted the scenic meadow as tourists fled in terror. The chilling video later revealed a man being fatally shot, highlighting the unexpected violence that shattered their vacation.
title: Kerala native's zip-lining video records chilling footage of Baisaran massacre

description: Samir Guha, a 56-year-old central government officer, tragically lost his life in the Pahalgam terror attack. His body was brought to his Kolkata home and laid at his beloved Bijoy Sangha Club's Durga mandap, where he was deeply involved in puja arrangements. His wife and daughter, who witnessed the horrific event, are devastated by the sudden loss.
title: Pahalgam massacre: Final farewells to Kolkata man at his beloved Durga mandap

description: Survivors of the Pahalgam tragedy recount the horror, stating terrorists recorded the massacre using bodycams. Sohini, widow of Bitan Adhikary, described how her husband was killed after admitting he was Hindu.
title: Pahalgam massacre: 'Killer had camera strapped to head, filmed hubby's death'

description: In a tragic incident, Bengaluru techie Bharath Bhushan was killed in a terrorist attack, as narrated by his wife Sujatha. Before being shot, Bharath comforted his family, urging them to stay strong. The terrorist questioned their happiness amidst suffering, then fatally shot Bharath after learning his name.
title: Pahalgam terror attack: Don't worry, stay strong, techie told wife in last words

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, India's decision to revoke Pakistani visas has cast a shadow over Pakistani Hindu families in Rajasthan. Radha Bheel, recently reunited with her toddler son after two years, now faces imminent separation as their short-term visas are cancelled.
title: Pakistani Hindu woman may lose son on short-term visa

description: Official sources responded to Pakistan's "act of war" statement, highlighting the implications of suspending the Simla Agreement, which effectively nullifies the Line of Control. This action raises concerns about the validity of nuclear and missile testing agreements, potentially escalating global tensions.
title: Putting Simla Agreement on hold absolves India of obligation to respect LoC

description: Shital, the widow of Shailesh Kalathiya, who was killed in a terrorist attack in Pahalgam, confronted visiting politicians, including Union Minister CR Paatil, expressing her grief and anger. She criticized the government's failure to protect citizens, questioning the heavy taxation against the lack of security.
title: We pay taxes but only VIPs get security, says grieving widow

description: Amidst India-Pakistan border tensions, a US State Department spokesperson declined to comment, affirming previous statements by US leaders. This follows unwavering US support for India after the deadly Pahalgam terrorist attack, which claimed 26 lives. US President Trump and Vice President Vance conveyed condolences to PM Modi, while Secretary Rubio pledged US solidarity.
title: 'Will say nothing more': US spokesperson shuns question on India-Pak tensions
